or, demonstrating romance to be a powerful framework for understanding how it works, and how it perseveres.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aDeserts in literature. 0aDesire in literature. 0aEast and West in literature. 0aErotic stories, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aHeroes in literature. 0aMasculinity in literature. 0aRomance fiction, AmericanxHistory and criticism. 0aSocial values in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Gothic & Romance.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9781479815616.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479896059zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781479896059/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA